# AgentSeam Core

AgentSeam is a lightweight approval layer for risky AI agent actions.

## Product Focus

- Prove the core loop first: propose action, approve or reject, execute or block, log result.
- Optimize for the smallest useful v1, not enterprise breadth.
- Keep the product web-first, cross-stack, and easy for developers to adopt.
- If scope is unclear, prefer the path that gets one end-to-end demo working sooner.

## Default Stack

- Next.js App Router app + pnpm workspace (`packages/sdk`, `packages/mcp-server`, `packages/mcp-proxy`)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Supabase for auth and Postgres
- Drizzle ORM
- Zod for validation
- pnpm only

## Build Principles

- Prefer boring, explicit implementations over clever abstractions.
- Keep files and functions small; extract only when reuse or clarity is obvious.
- Make state transitions explicit, especially for action lifecycle changes.
- Validate all external input at the boundary.
- Keep the SDK tiny; do not turn it into a framework.

## Guardrails

- The core approval loop is proven. Continue to prefer focused, incremental features over enterprise breadth.
- Do not add realtime, policy engines, or broad governance features without a clear product reason.
- Keep the UI cleaner and simpler than the backend.
- When product intent is ambiguous, consult `agentseam-project-outline.txt`.
